  <recipe id="Peppermint Cookies">
    <head>
      <title>Peppermint Cookies</title>
      <source>Mollie Helton</source>
      <categories>
        <cat class="main">Cookies</cat>
        <cat class="region">America</cat>
				<cat class="diet">Nut-free</cat>
      </categories>
    </head>
    <description><xhtml:p>I began eating these when I was a little girl and since then, they have always been my favorite Christmas Cookies.</xhtml:p></description>
    <ingredients system="US">
      <ing-div>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1 1/4</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>crushed peppermints</item>
<!--1 1/4 c. crushed peppermints-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1 1/3</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>sugar</item>
          <prep>divided</prep>
<!--1 1/3 c. sugar, divided (1/3 c. for topping, 1 c. for dough)-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3/4</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>butter</item>
<!--3/4 c. butter-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
          </amt>
          <item>eggs</item>
<!--2 eggs-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>tsp</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>peppermint extract</item>
<!--1 tsp. peppermint extract-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3/4</qty>
            <unit>tsp</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>vanilla</item>
<!--3/4 tsp. vanilla-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2 1/2</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>flour</item>
<!--2 1/2 c. flour-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>tsp</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>salt</item>
<!--1/4 tsp. salt-->
        </ing>
      </ing-div>
    </ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>Grind peppermint candies in 1/3 c. sugar until powdery with a few larger chunks of candies. This is best done with a food processor.</step>
      <step>Mix flour and salt in a small bowl. Mix butter, eggs, and remaining 1 c. sugar together in a separate, larger bowl. Add vanilla and peppermint extracts.</step>
      <step>Add flour mixture in 3 parts to sugar mixture until well mixed. Form dough into small balls, about an inch or so wide. Roll the balls of dough in the crushed candy mixture and place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 8 minutes in an oven preheated to <temp><qty>350</qty><tempunit unit="F" system="US">degrees</tempunit><!--350  degrees--></temp>.</step>
      <step>Remove cookies from oven and let cool on baking sheet for 1 minute, then remove them and roll them in the mixture once more before placing them on a sheet of wax paper to cool.</step>
      <step>Enjoy!!</step>
    </directions>
  </recipe>
